OL,6,FThe judge, Tom Bayliss KC, told them:
OL,7,F"What happened that summer evening
OL,8,Fserves as a chilling example of how a
OL,9,Fviolent, anarchic mob can, with
OL,10,Fastonishing ease, achieve complete
OL,11,Flawlessness.
OL,13,F"It also offers a dystopian vision of
OL,14,Fwhat can happen when the rule of law
OL,15,Fis subverted by mob violence."
OL,17,FDobre, 37, of Clifton Mount, Leeds,
OL,18,Fadmitted arson with recklessness as to
OL,19,Fwhether life was endangered. He was
OL,20,Fjailed for six years.
